The length of the ban ensured Inter could not pursue the deal for Cantona - and Sampdoria changed their mind about selling Mancini, meaning neither player moved to the San Siro.

In Corriere, Moratti is quoted as saying: 'Then Cantona did it.

'In London, with me present, this kung-fu kick of the Crystal Palace fan.

'And then he wanted to stay in Manchester, while Sampdoria then decided that they would not let Mancini leave.'

Cantona subsequently remained at United until he retired in 1997.

He scored in 80 goals in 185 games for the club after signing from Leeds United in 1992.

